HEADWORD: Fungous
<hw>Fun"gous</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>fungosus</ets>: cf. F. <ets>fungueux</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>Of the nature of fungi; spongy.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><-- p. 604 --></p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Growing suddenly, but not substantial or
durable.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Fungus</ent>⟦br⟧
